# SuperHabits — Project Rules

## Project identity
SuperHabits is an offline-first React Native + Expo app with 5 modules:
todos, habits, pomodoro, workout, calories.
Stack: React Native 0.83, Expo 55, TypeScript 5.9, expo-router, SQLite
(expo-sqlite WAL mode), NativeWind 4, React Query 5, Vitest.
Target: Web (PWA), iOS, Android.
Status: Active MVP. No production deployment pipeline yet.
Current stored schema version: **9** (see `app_meta.db_schema_version`). Next migration: add a new **`if (version < 10) { ... }`** block in `runMigrations()` in `core/db/client.ts` when a schema change lands.

## Non-negotiable invariants — violating these causes silent data corruption

1. SOFT DELETE ONLY
   Never use DELETE FROM on main entity tables (todos, habits, habit_completions
   is the exception, workout_logs, calorie_entries, pomodoro_sessions).
   Always set deleted_at = datetime('now') and filter WHERE deleted_at IS NULL.
   Hard delete = data loss with no recovery path.

2. SYNC ENQUEUE ON EVERY WRITE
   Every INSERT/UPDATE on main entities must call syncEngine.enqueue(record)
   immediately after the DB operation.
   Exceptions (intentionally not synced): pomodoro_sessions, workout_logs,
   habit_completions.
   Missing enqueue = silent sync gap when cloud sync is enabled.

3. DB SINGLETON MUST INITIALIZE BEFORE ANY DATA ACCESS
   All data functions call await getDatabase() at the start.
   Never open a second SQLite connection. Never access db before init.
   Breaking the singleton breaks the entire app on cold start.

4. IDs VIA createId(prefix) ONLY
   Never use Math.random(), crypto.randomUUID(), or raw timestamps as IDs.
   Format: {prefix}_{timestamp}_{random8} — enforced in lib/id.ts.
   Prefix must match the entity: "todo", "habit", "cal", "wrk", "pom".

5. DATE KEYS VIA toDateKey() ONLY
   All YYYY-MM-DD date strings must come from toDateKey() in lib/time.ts.
   Since migration 5, toDateKey() uses the device’s **local** calendar date
   (YYYY-MM-DD). Rows written before migration 5 used UTC calendar dates;
   see `app_meta.date_key_cutover` — no silent backfill of old rows.

6. MIGRATIONS ARE APPEND-ONLY AND MONOTONICALLY INCREASING
   Never modify an existing migration. Always add a new file numbered N+1.
   Current stored version: 9. Next migration number: 10 (new `if (version < 10)` block in `runMigrations` in `core/db/client.ts`).
   Migration logic runs in core/db/client.ts — append a new block in runMigrations() (if (version < N)).
   schema.sql is a reference doc only — it is NOT executed at runtime.

7. UNIQUE(habit_id, date_key) on habit_completions
   The data layer (habits.data.ts) avoids duplicate rows by:
   - SELECT for an existing row matching (habit_id, date_key)
   - INSERT with createId("hcmp") if none exists; UPDATE count if it does
   - On decrement to zero: DELETE that row (hard delete — allowed exception for this table)
   Do not change this pattern without reviewing UNIQUE and sync implications.

## File naming conventions
- Source files: camelCase (e.g. todoHelpers.ts)
- React components: PascalCase (e.g. TodoCard.tsx)
- Data layer: {feature}.data.ts (e.g. todos.data.ts)
- Domain/pure logic: {feature}.domain.ts (e.g. habits.domain.ts)
- Screens: {Feature}Screen.tsx (e.g. TodosScreen.tsx)
- Route wrappers: app/(tabs)/{feature}.tsx — thin, just renders the Screen

## Adding a new feature — required structure
features/{name}/
  {name}.data.ts      ← all SQLite CRUD, exports typed functions
  {name}.domain.ts    ← pure logic, no DB imports, fully testable
  {name}Screen.tsx    ← React Native UI, imports from .data and .domain

Route file: app/(tabs)/{name}.tsx → renders {Name}Screen
Tab entry: app/(tabs)/_layout.tsx → add tab icon + href

## Unused dependencies — do NOT add usage without discussion
The following are installed but intentionally unused:
- zustand (state management — may be used for future global state)
- @tanstack/react-query (no hooks used — QueryClient provided but dormant)
- date-fns (listed in package.json, not imported anywhere in source)
- expo-background-fetch, expo-task-manager (deferred background sync)
Do not wire these up without an explicit decision to do so.

## Testing requirements
- Every new *.domain.ts function must have a Vitest unit test
- Test files live in tests/ directory
- Run: npm test
- Current count: 143 tests passing — **update this count whenever tests are added or removed**
- No DB or component tests yet — do not block on this, but document gaps

## E2E Tests (Playwright)

E2E tests live in `e2e/` at the project root. They run against the **static web export** in `dist/`, served by `node scripts/serve-e2e.js` on `http://localhost:8081` with `Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp` (OPFS + SQLite WASM). **Playwright does not build the app:** run `npm run build:web` yourself whenever React components or web bundle output change, then run E2E. Metro (`npm run web`) is for local dev with HMR — **not** used by the E2E pipeline.

**Test files:**
- `e2e/todos.spec.ts` — Todos feature
- `e2e/habits.spec.ts` — Habits feature
- `e2e/pomodoro.spec.ts` — Pomodoro feature
- `e2e/workout.spec.ts` — Workout feature
- `e2e/calories.spec.ts` — Calories feature
- `e2e/infrastructure.spec.ts` — Headers, SW, OPFS, DB init

**Config:** `playwright.config.ts`
- `headless: true` always
- Chromium only
- `workers: 1` locally (do not increase — OPFS + expo-sqlite hold one lock per origin; extra workers cause flaky navigation/reload). `fullyParallel: false` — tests in a file stay serial; `clearDatabase()` in `beforeEach` must not race.
- `webServer.command`: `node scripts/serve-e2e.js` (serves `dist/`; ensure `npm run build:web` has been run)
- `retries: 2` on CI, `0` locally
- HTML report: `.cursor/playwright-output/e2e-report/`
- Failure screenshots / traces: `.cursor/playwright-output/e2e-failures/` (`outputDir`)

**Commands:**
- `npm run e2e` — run all E2E tests
- `npm run e2e:report` — open HTML report
- `npm run e2e:headed` — run with visible browser (debug only)
- `npm run e2e:debug` — Playwright inspector

**Slash commands:**
- `/test` — run unit tests + E2E tests in one pass
- `/e2e-fix` — run E2E, read report via Playwright MCP, auto-fix

**E2E invariants:**
- `clearDatabase()` called in `test.beforeEach` (not `afterEach`)
- `e2e/global.setup.ts` aborts if `crossOriginIsolated` is false
- Do not add `data-testid` to app components
- Do not change assertions to make tests pass artificially
- If a test reveals a genuine bug, fix the app not the test
- E2E tests are NOT unit tests — they require the static server (or CI’s `build:web` + `npm run e2e`)

## CI (GitHub Actions)

Two jobs (see `.github/workflows/ci.yml`):
- **quality** — typecheck + unit tests (runs first)
- **e2e** — Playwright Chromium tests (runs only if **quality** passes); runs `npm run build:web`, then `npm run e2e` (Playwright starts `node scripts/serve-e2e.js` per `webServer` in `playwright.config.ts`)

## Current known bugs (do not silently fix — coordinate first)
- Sync flush is gated on isRemoteEnabled() (lib/supabase.ts) — interval / visibility / NetInfo flush
  runs only when remote is enabled. While remote is off (default), the in-memory sync queue can grow
  with NoopSyncAdapter; this is intentional until cloud sync is turned on. Document as a tradeoff, not
  a silent bug fix.
- schema.sql is out of date (reference only, not authoritative)

Resolved in repo (do not re-report as open): CaloriesScreen passes user-selected `mealType` to `addCalorieEntry` (meal type picker); `syncEngine.flush()` is wired in `AppProviders` when `isRemoteEnabled()` is true. **toDateKey()** now uses local calendar dates (migration 5 records `date_key_format` / `date_key_cutover` in `app_meta`).

Implementation note: `nextPomodoroState` in `features/pomodoro/pomodoro.domain.ts` is covered by Vitest; **PomodoroScreen** currently uses inline button labels and does not import it — wire the screen to the domain helper if you want a single source of truth for `Running...` vs `Start focus`.

## Web / PWA context (not application bugs)
- **COEP:** `metro.config.js` and `app.json` set `Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp` (was `credentialless` in some setups) to establish `crossOriginIsolated` for shared-memory WASM on web.
- **Service worker:** `public/sw.js` uses cache name `superhabits-shell-v2` (`CACHE_VERSION = "v2"`). **Dev bypass:** requests to `localhost` / `127.0.0.1` use network-first `fetch` (no stale Metro cache).

## MCP tools (development)
Configured in the user’s MCP settings (e.g. `~/.cursor/mcp.json` on Unix; equivalent on Windows). Useful servers for this repo:
- **Playwright MCP** — live browser inspection; use with `/inspect-web`, `/pre-pr`, and `/e2e-fix`.
- **Lighthouse MCP** — performance, PWA, accessibility; use with `/audit-performance`.
- **Fetch MCP** — HTTP header verification (e.g. COOP/COEP); use in `/audit-performance` phase 1.

**Slash commands (summary):** `/inspect-web`, `/pre-pr`, `/audit-performance`, `/test` (unit + E2E), `/e2e-fix` (E2E run + report-driven fixes).
